urls.title: Even With Cardboard Beds And Recycled Medals, Olympics Take Flak Over The Environment
urls.description: Tokyo 2020 aims to be the most environmentally friendly games, offsetting carbon emissions and using sustainable materials. But some environmental groups say the symbolism exaggerates the reality.

data.text:
The Tokyo Olympics is branding itself as the most eco-friendly games ever — using recycled materials and giving athletes cardboard beds, for example.But some analysts say that symbolism exaggerates the reality. Others say it's straight-up "greenwashing."
 https://t.co/P2iysBaZUn
